          "title": "Apache Flink Applications",
          "helpText": "The general guidance we provide prior to testing your application is 1 MB per second per KPU. However, we recommend that you test your application with production loads to get an accurate estimate of the number of KPUs required for your application. KPUs usage can vary considerably based on your data volume and velocity, code complexity, integrations, and more. This is especially true when using the Apache Flink runtime in Amazon Kinesis Data Analytics. For example, through internal testing we have observed throughput of hundreds of MB per second per KPU for simple applications with no state; and throughput less than 1 MB per second per KPU for complex applications that utilize intensive machine learning algorithms.",
